    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.2.4-5"/>
                <note type="curatorial">4</note>
                <note type="curatorial">Piper Collection</note>
                
                <opener>
                    
                    <dateline>
                        Sat after-noon 
                        Nov. 6-1920 
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>My Dear girlie;</salute>
                    
                </opener>
                
                <p>I wonder if this will reach you in time so that you can meet us at the Station as we go thu tomorrow (Sun) afternoon on our way to the Ozarks. I feel that I must see you before leaving.</p> 
                <p>Evry thing has been done in such a hurry that I am all dazed, and about all I do konw is that I must see you first a a minute</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.2.4-5"/>
                <note type="curatorial">5</note>
                
                <p>my Dear little girl I love you just the same always.</p>

                <signed>Alice M. Neihardt</signed> 
            </div1>
            
            <div1 type="address">
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    BANCROFT 
                    3PM
                    NOV
                    6
                    1920
                    NEB.
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="stamp">
                    UNITED STATES <figure/> 3 CENTS
                </ab> 
                
                <ab type="address">
                    Miss Mildred Piper 
                    Lyons Nebr. 
                </ab> 
                
            </div1>
            
